BcsecAuthenticatable
====================

This is a Devise (https://github.com/plataformatec/devise) strategy for Northwestern's bcsec authentication system.


Installation
============

To use bcsec as nucore's authentication strategy please do the following:

1. In this plugin's config/environments directory copy the *.template files to the same dir.
   Leave the filename the same, but drop the ".template". Update the authority information in the new files.

2. In the User class, replace the existing call to #devise with "devise :bcsec_authenticatable"

3. Update app/views/sessions/new.html.haml to use a form like this:

- form_for resource_name, resource, :url => session_path(resource_name) do |f|
    %ul.form
      %li
        %label== Username
        = text_field_tag :username, params[:username], :size => 30
      %li
        %label== Password
        = password_field_tag :password, nil, :size => 15
    %ul.horiz
      %li= submit_tag 'Login', :class => 'btn'


In other words, have the form submit parameters 'username' and 'password', not 'user[username]' and 'user[password]'
like Devise's database_authenticatable expects.